As lor my- self, l say that one should see whether the right oi possession of the defeated and third parties is the same or not, for in the second situation it would surely be a more correct and the common view that a verdict pronounced against one person does not injure a third party who knows and is in possession, but this third party will be able to hinder execution on the ground ol possession only. Jason gives evidence of this common opinion and sets it forth, and Cravetta does not oppose it in this connection, or does not oppose it effectively. But it there is the same right oi possession for both, one ought 180 not to doubt that a verdict injures the third party; for instance, a verdict brought against a tenant, who holds possession lor an owner, injures the owner; one pronounced against a navigator, who holds possession lor owners‚ will injure the owners. ¹¹¹¹Surely he “in whose name possession is held ” holds possession. “ An agent gives his services in behall of another’s possession,” and the possession in this case of that other person is real.
